---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";

const title = "Terms and conditions";
const description = "Terms and conditions";
---

<Base
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonicalPath="/terms-and-conditions"
>
  <Section>
    <article class="prose">
      <h1>Terms and conditions of ticket sales for CAKE conf event</h1>
      <h2>§ 1. General provisions</h2>
      <p>
        These terms and conditions set out the rules for purchasing and using
        tickets for the “CAKE conf” event (hereinafter referred to as the
        “Event”).
      </p>
      <p>
        The organizer of the Event is the Content Bytes Foundation (hereinafter
        referred to as the “Organizer”).
      </p>
      <p>
        Purchase of a ticket constitutes acceptance of these terms and
        conditions.
      </p>
      <h2>§ 2. Ticket sales</h2>
      <p>
        Tickets are sold electronically via the official Event website or via a
        ticketing platform indicated by the Organizer.
      </p>
      <p>Ticket prices are gross prices and are exempt from VAT.</p>
      <p>
        The ticket entitling entry to the Event is the confirmation (electronic
        or printed) sent to the Buyer’s email address after payment has been
        processed.
      </p>
      <h2>§ 3. Refunds and no refund policy</h2>
      <p>The Organizer does not provide refunds for purchased tickets.</p>
      <p>
        Once payment has been completed and the purchase finalized, the Buyer is
        not entitled to a refund, regardless of the reason for non-attendance at
        the Event.
      </p>
      <h2>§ 4. Non-transferability and ticket personalization</h2>
      <p>
        Each ticket is personalized and assigned to the specific Participant
        indicated during the purchase process.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Organizer does not allow ticket transfers to another person or
        changes to Participant data after the purchase has been completed.
      </p>
      <p>
        Entry to the Event will only be granted to the person whose name appears
        on the ticket and who presents a valid identity document at the
        entrance.
      </p>
      <h2>§ 5. Photography and recording</h2>
      <p>
        The Event may be photographed and/or video recorded. By attending the
        Event, Participants acknowledge and agree that their image may be
        recorded as part of such materials.
      </p>
      <p>
        Photographs and video recordings may be used by the Organizer for
        documentation, promotional, and marketing purposes, including
        publication on websites, social media channels, and other communication
        materials related to the Organizer’s activities.
      </p>
      <h2>§ 6. Final provisions</h2>
      <p>
        In matters not regulated by these terms and conditions, the provisions
        of the Polish Civil Code shall apply.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Organizer reserves the right to make changes to the Event agenda due
        to circumstances beyond its control.
      </p>
      <p>
        These terms and conditions enter into force on the date ticket sales
        begin.
      </p>
    </article>
  </Section>
</Base>

<style>
  .prose h2 {
    color: white;
  }
</style>
